Package: groovyJCSP

[Groovy] Class ChannelOutputList

    • groovyJCSP.ChannelOutputList

    • Title: Groovy Classes to Implement JCSP parallelism

      Description: Classes required to implement JCSP Constructs within Groovy

      Copyright: Copyright (c) 2005

      Company: Napier University

      Version:
      1.0
      1.1 included the empty constructor to enable easier NetChannelOUTPUT list creation (Jon Kerridge) and changes to comply with Groovy-jsr03
      Authors:
      Jon Kerridge, Ken Barclay, John Savage

          Constructors 
          Constructor and description
          ChannelOutputList (jcsp.lang.Any2AnyChannel[] channelArray)
          ChannelOutputList uses the ArrayList class of java This ChannelOutputList takes an array of Any2Any Channels as its constructor parameter and converts them to a list of Channel Output Ends

          ChannelOutputList ()
          ChannelOutputList uses the ArrayList class of java This constructor creates an empty ArrayList to be populated with Channel Output Ends

      • Method Detail

        • void append(jcsp.lang.ChannelOutput value)

          Appends the channel output end or net channel output to the ChannelOutputList.

          Parameters:
          value - The channel end to be added to the list of channels

        • @groovy.transform.CompileDynamic void broadcast(java.lang.Object bValue)

          The broadcast method writes the same cloned value to each element of the ChannelOutputList. The channels are written to in parallel

          Parameters:
          value - The value to be written, which must implement Cloneable

        • @groovy.transform.CompileDynamic void broadcastSeq(java.lang.Object value)

          The broadcastSeq method writes the cloned value to each element of the ChannelOutputList. The channels are written to in sequence

          Parameters:
          value - The value to be written, which must implement Cloneable

        • boolean contains(jcsp.lang.ChannelOutput value)

          The method contains determines whether or not the Channel Output List contains a specific value

          Returns:
          a boolean such that if value is contained in the Channel Output List true is returned and false otherwise
          Parameters:
          value - The element value which is to be looked for

        • jcsp.lang.ChannelOutput getAt(int index)

          This method returns the channel output end located at the subscript specified by index

          Returns:
          the ChannelOutputEnd at subscript index
          Parameters:
          index - the subscript of the channel end returned form the ChannelOutputList

        • void putAt(int index, jcsp.lang.ChannelOutput value)

          This method puts a channel end specified by value at the position specified by index into the channel list

          Returns:
          the channel list with the element subscripted by index set to value
          Parameters:
          index - the subscript of the element to be set
          value - a channel output end

        • boolean remove(jcsp.lang.ChannelOutput value)

          This method removes a value that is a channel output end from the list

          Returns:
          boolean indicating whether the required element has been removed
          Parameters:
          value - the channel output end to be removed

        • int size()

          Returns the length of the Channel Output List

          Returns:
          the number of elements in the Channel Output List

        • jcsp.lang.ChannelOutput[] toArray()

          converts the ChannelOutputList to an array

          Returns:
          the array of ChannelOutputEnds

        • void write(java.util.List valueList)

          The write method writes to each channel in a ChannelOutputList a value from the list of values, one value per channel end, both subscripted using the same index. The channels are written to in parallel

          Parameters:
          valueList - A list containing the values to be written one for each channel in the ChannelOutputList

        • void writeSeq(java.util.List valueList)

          The writeSeq method writes to each channel in a ChannelOutputList a value from the list of values, one value per channel end, both subscripted using the same index. The channels are written to in sequence

          Parameters:
          valueList - A list containing the values to be written one for each channel in the ChannelOutputList
